Simple Type MeasurementKind
Namespace No namespace
Annotations
 
Tooltip:<br/> The type of measurement, Naming and enumeration options are in alignment with those from Green Button Connect
Element naming is aligned with the CIM semantic model: https://ontology.tno.nl/cerise/cim-profile/cim_ReadingType.measurementKind.html
OWL ontology at: https://ontology.tno.nl/IEC_CIM.ttl
                
Identifies "what" is being measured, as refinement of 'commodity'. When combined with 'unit', it provides detail to the unit of measure. For example, 'energy' with a unit of measure of 'kWh' indicates to the user that active energy is being measured, while with 'kVAh' or 'kVArh', it indicates apparent energy and reactive energy, respectively. 'power' can be combined in a similar way with various power units of measure: Distortion power ('distortionVoltAmperes') with 'kVA' is different from 'power' with 'kVA'.

Type restriction of xs:string

enumeration batteryCarryover
enumeration batteryVoltage

enumeration demandLimit
enumeration distance
enumeration energy
enumeration frequency

enumeration phasorReactivePower
enumeration power
enumeration powerFactor
enumeration powerQuality
enumeration voltage
enumeration volumetricFlow
enumeration

When combined with 'unit', it provides detail to the unit of measure.
